irc2 - a shell-based irc client

A minimal solution that uses netcat creating quick Internet Relay Chat
(IRC) connections. 

Usage
-----

Usage: irc2 [<server>] [<port>] [<nick>] [<username>] [<realname>]

Installation
------------

git clone http://github.com/mcpcpc/irc2
cd ircc
sudo install -Dm755 ircc "/usr/bin"

Examples
--------

To connect to a Freenode server:
	irc2 irc.freenode.net 6667 mcpcpc

Once connected, you can specify a channel to join (using "/[command]").
Note that this will also set the default message channel:
	/join #kisslinux

To send a message to the recently joined channel, just type a message:
	hello world!

Contact
-------

For questions or issues, please contact info [at] mcpcpc [dot] com.

